==English==
===Etymology===
From the United States Army [[acronym]] "'''A'''bsent '''W'''ith'''o'''ut '''L'''eave"

===Adjective===
# (''[[military|Mil.]] and [[generic]]'') Absent without [[leave]] ([[permission]]).
#:''The US Army has a lot of AWOL soldiers.''

===Noun===

# (''[[military|Mil.]]'') The status of being absent from the command and control of a military organization without being placed on leave, detached to another unit, or otherwise receiving official sanction for an absence
# (''[[military|Mil.]]'') A person who holds AWOL status.
# (''[[generic]]'') Somebody who is absent without permission.

===Usage===

The United States [[Marine]] Corps uses the term "UA" (''Unauthorized Absence'') instead of "AWOL".